<subSubSection id="B380651AFF85E228FF5290E8D4585AA4" pageId="9" pageNumber="390" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FB253691FF85E228FF5290E8D4585AA4" blockId="9.[151,1436,1930,2027]" pageId="9" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis id="C9EEEA83FF85E228FF5290E8D7385A88" bold="true" box="[199,334,1966,1991]" pageId="9" pageNumber="390">Etymology.</emphasis>
Latin 
<emphasis id="C9EEEA83FF85E228FE0390E9D79C5A89" box="[406,490,1967,1990]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="390">niger—</emphasis>
black, 
<emphasis id="C9EEEA83FF85E228FDA090E8D4F05A88" box="[565,646,1966,1991]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="390">linea—</emphasis>
a line. The species name alludes to the characteristic, short but distinct black streak in fold on the forewing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
